<li id="cite_note-HRCPL1374-14">^ <a href="#cite_ref-HRCPL1374_14-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRCPL1374_14-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRCPL1374_14-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRCPL1374_14-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRCPL1374_14-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-HRCPL1374_14-5" title=""><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#CITEREFClarkBriggsCooke2005" title="">Clark, Briggs &amp; Cooke 2005</a>, p.&#160;1374</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFProctor1997">Proctor, Robert (1997), "<a href="http://environmentaloncology.org/files/file/secrethistorysupport/Chapt%203%20References/REF%207%20proctor.pdf" class="external text" title="http://environmentaloncology.org/files/file/secrethistorysupport/Chapt%203%20References/REF%207%20proctor.pdf" rel="nofollow">The Nazi War on Tobacco: Ideology, Evidence, and Possible Cancer Consequences</a>" (PDF), <i><a href="/wiki/Bulletin_of_the_History_of_Medicine" title="Bulletin of the History of Medicine">Bulletin of the History of Medicine</a></i> <b>71</b> (3): 435–88, <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9302840" class="external" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9302840">PMID 9302840</a><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://environmentaloncology.org/files/file/secrethistorysupport/Chapt%203%20References/REF%207%20proctor.pdf" class="external free" title="http://environmentaloncology.org/files/file/secrethistorysupport/Chapt%203%20References/REF%207%20proctor.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://environmentaloncology.org/files/file/secrethistorysupport/Chapt%203%20References/REF%207%20proctor.pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2008-07-22</span>,  "The first German antitobacco organization was established in 1904 (the short-lived Deutscher Tabakgegnerverein zum Schutze für Nichtraucher); this was followed by a Bund Deutscher Tabakgegner based in the town of Trautenau, in Bohemia (1910), and similar associations in Hanover and Dresden (both founded in 1912). When Czechoslovakia was severed from Austria after the First World War, a Bund Deutscher Tabakgegner in der Tschechoslowakei was established in Prague (1920); that same year in Graz a Bund Deutscher Tabakgegner in Deutschösterreich was founded."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Nazi+War+on+Tobacco%3A+Ideology%2C+Evidence%2C+and+Possible+Cancer+Consequences&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BBulletin+of+the+History+of+Medicine%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Proctor&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.au=Proctor%2C+Robert&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.volume=71&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=435%E2%80%9388&amp;rft_id=info:pmid/9302840&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fenvironmentaloncology.org%2Ffiles%2Ffile%2Fsecrethistorysupport%2FChapt%25203%2520References%2FREF%25207%2520proctor.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Anti-tobacco_movement_in_Nazi_Germany"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
